54a5eaa57635a3d24cfdfe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident-elect%20Donald%20Trump's%20stance%20on%20a%20TikTok%20ban%20has%20changed%20over%20time%2C%20but%20his%20cabinet%20picks%20have%20been%20more%20resolute.%3Cp%3EJaap%20Arriens%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPresident-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20once%20supported%20a%20US%20ban%20on%20TikTok.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThen%2C%20during%20the%202024%20presidential%20campaign%2C%20Trump%20said%20he%20would%20%26quot%3Bsave%20TikTok.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20cabinet%20picks%20might%20indicate%20what%20position%20he'll%20ultimately%20take%20once%20in%20office.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident-elect%20Donald%20Trump's%20views%20on%20whether%20TikTok%2C%20which%20a%20Chinese%20company%20owns%2C%20poses%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20United%20States%20have%20shifted%20180%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWill%20they%20come%20full%20circle%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20lawmakers%20concerned%20about%20Chinese%20influence%20passed%20a%20law%20giving%20ByteDance%2C%20the%20Chinese%20owner%20of%20TikTok%2C%20a%20deadline%20of%20January%2019%20to%20sell%20its%20social%20media%20app%20to%20a%20non-Chinese%20company%20or%20face%20a%20nationwide%20ban.%20TikTok%20appealed%2C%20but%20on%20Friday%2C%20a%20federal%20court%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-details-when-how-legal-cases-trump-options%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupheld%20the%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20siding%20with%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20argument%20that%20the%20service%20poses%20a%20national%20security%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20Trump%20unsuccessfully%20sought%20to%20ban%20TikTok%20in%20the%20United%20States%20but%20has%20since%20had%20a%20change%20of%20heart.%20During%20the%202024%20campaign%2C%20Trump%20said%20young%20people%20would%20%26quot%3Bgo%20crazy%20without%20it.%26quot%3B%20Trump's%20own%20TikTok%20accounts%20generated%20millions%20of%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20side%20Trump%20ultimately%20lands%20on%20the%20issue%20could%20have%20a%20major%20impact%20on%20ByteDance%20and%20TikTok%2C%20which%20says%20it%20has%20over%20170%20million%20users%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20Even%20if%20the%20law%20is%20upheld%20after%20future%20appeals%2C%20Trump%20could%20choose%20not%20to%20enforce%20it%20during%20his%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20closest%20advisors%2C%20however%2C%20might%20have%20something%20to%20say%20about%20that.%20Some%20of%20Trump's%20top%20cabinet%20nominees%20support%20a%20TikTok%20ban.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Marco%20Rubio%20of%20Florida%20%E2%80%94%20Trump's%20nominee%20for%20secretary%20of%20state%20%E2%80%94%20called%20a%20ban%20a%20%26quot%3Bwin%20for%20America%26quot%3B%20earlier%20this%20year.%20Trump's%20pick%20for%20Federal%20Communications%20Commission%20chair%2C%20Brendan%20Carr%2C%20also%20advocated%20for%20a%20TikTok%20ban%20in%20Project%202025%2C%20a%20road%20map%20for%20the%20first%20180%20days%20of%20a%20new%20Republican%20presidency%20that%20the%20Heritage%20Foundation%2C%20a%20conservative%20think%20tank%2C%20published%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarr%20wrote%20in%20the%20plan%20that%20TikTok%20is%20part%20of%20a%20Beijing%20%26quot%3Bforeign%20influence%20campaign%20by%20determining%20the%20news%20and%20information%20that%20the%20app%20feeds%20to%20millions%20of%20Americans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProject%202025%20refers%20to%20TikTok%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20tool%20of%20Chinese%20espionage%26quot%3B%20that%20is%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20addictive%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bespecially%20popular%20with%20teenage%20girls.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ties%20between%20TikTok%20and%20the%20Chinese%20government%20are%20not%20loose%2C%20and%20they%20are%20not%20coincidental%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Ratcliffe%2C%20the%20former%20US%20director%20of%20national%20intelligence%2C%20is%20Trump's%20pick%20for%20CIA%20director.%20Ratcliffe%2C%20also%20an%20author%20of%20Project%202025%2C%20told%20Fox%20News%20in%202022%20that%20he%20thinks%20TikTok%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bnational%20security%20threat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovs.%20Doug%20Burgum%20of%20North%20Dakota%2C%20Trump's%20pick%20for%20interior%20secretary%2C%20and%20Kristi%20Noem%20of%20South%20Dakota%2C%20the%20president-elect's%20choice%20for%20Homeland%20Security%20secretary%2C%20both%20previously%20banned%20the%20app%20from%20state-owned%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20has%20denied%20accusations%20that%20it%20influences%20content%20inside%20the%20United%20States%20or%20is%20addictive%20to%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20TikTok%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20TikTok%20ban%20law%20was%20%26quot%3Bconceived%20and%20pushed%20through%20based%20upon%20inaccurate%2C%20flawed%20and%20hypothetical%20information%2C%20resulting%20in%20outright%20censorship%20of%20the%20American%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20an%20established%20historical%20record%20of%20protecting%20Americans'%20right%20to%20free%20speech%2C%20and%20we%20expect%20they%20will%20do%20just%20that%20on%20this%20important%20constitutional%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-trump-cabinet-influence-project-2025-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733686711000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6754a76fa57635a3d24cfe0d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-trump-cabinet-influence-project-2025-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20once%20sought%20to%20ban%20TikTok%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20now%20says%20he'll%20%26quot%3Bsave%26quot%3B%20it.%20His%20cabinet%20picks%2