escalation%20in%20deadly%20attacks%20in%20recent%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20stated%20that%20we%20need%20a%20just%20and%20enduring%20peace%20--%20one%20that%20the%20Russians%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20destroy%20in%20a%20few%20years%2C%20as%20they%20have%20done%20repeatedly%20in%20the%20past%2C%26quot%3B%20Zelensky%20said%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%20three%20years%20of%20war%20have%20ravaged%20Ukraine%2C%20leaving%20thousands%20dead%20and%20millions%20fleeing%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUkrainians%20want%20peace%20more%20than%20anyone%20else.%20Russia%20brought%20war%20to%20our%20land%2C%20and%20it%20is%20Russia%20that%20most%20seeks%20to%20disrupt%20the%20possibility%20of%20peace%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20called%20on%20Western%20allies%20not%20to%20%26quot%3Bturn%20a%20blind%20eye%20to%20occupation%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20Kyiv%20would%20only%20agree%20to%20a%20deal%20that%20will%20bring%20long-term%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWar%20cannot%20be%20endless%20--%20only%20peace%20must%20be%20permanent%20and%20reliable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20rare%20admission%20of%20numbers%2C%20Zelensky%20said%2043%2C000%20Ukrainian%20troops%20had%20been%20killed%20in%20combat%2C%20while%20some%20370%2C000%20were%20wounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20sides%20are%20believed%20to%20have%20suffered%20massive%20casualties%20and%20that%20figure%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20far%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Key%20conditions'%20discussed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZelensky%20gave%20no%20concrete%20details%20on%20key%20aspects%20of%20what%20negotiations%20could%20look%20like%2C%20but%20a%20senior%20Ukrainian%20official%20said%20they%20had%20discussed%20%26quot%3Bsome%20key%20conditions%26quot%3B%20for%20ending%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20not%20disclosing%20details%2C%20but%20the%20presidents%20discussed%20at%20the%20meeting%20that%20there%20should%20be%20something%20that%20would%20guarantee%20the%20reliability%20of%20the%20peace%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20source%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20accused%20Ukraine%20of%20%26quot%3Brefusing%26quot%3B%20to%20negotiate%20an%20end%20to%20the%20war%20and%20said%20its%20conditions%20to%20enter%20peace%20talks%20--%20which%20include%20Kyiv%20giving%20up%20four%20regions%20--%20remain%20unchanged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Ukrainian%20side%20refused%20and%20is%20refusing%20negotiation%2C%26quot%3B%20Kremlin%20spokesman%20Dmitry%20Peskov%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20referred%20to%20a%202022%20Ukrainian%20decree%20that%20ruled%20out%20talks%20with%20Putin%2C%20but%20not%20other%20Russian%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20had%20earlier%20called%20for%20an%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20ceasefire%26quot%3B%20and%20called%20for%20talks%20to%20begin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToo%20many%20lives%20are%20being%20so%20needlessly%20wasted%2C%20too%20many%20families%20destroyed%2C%20and%20if%20it%20keeps%20going%2C%20it%20can%20turn%20into%20something%20much%20bigger%2C%20and%20far%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20on%20his%20Truth%20Social%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20touted%20himself%20as%20having%20good%20relations%20with%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'How%20long%20can%20we%20be%20at%20war%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20leaders%20made%20statements%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20Moscow%20and%20Paris%2C%20the%20situation%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine%20remained%20dire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoscow%20claimed%20another%20village%20in%20the%20east%20--%20Blagodatne%20in%20the%20Donetsk%20region%20--%20on%20Sunday%2C%20pressing%20steady%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20in%20Ukraine%20have%20feared%20that%20Trump%20taking%20office%20would%20force%20it%20to%20make%20heart-aching%20concessions%20to%20Russia%2C%20while%20the%20nation%20is%20also%20suffering%20exhaustion.%