gain%20control%20over%20the%20entire%20Aleppo%20by%20the%20end%20of%202016.%20Since%20then%2C%20conflict%20in%20Syria%20has%20been%20majorly%20static%20with%20the%20rebels%20largely%20confined%20to%20the%20Idlib%20governate%2C%20adjacent%20to%20the%20Aleppo%20governate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20after%20years%20locked%20behind%20frozen%20frontlines%2C%20Syrian%20rebels%20have%20burst%20forth%20to%20mount%20the%20swiftest%20battlefield%20advance%20by%20either%20side%20since%20a%20rebellion%20against%20President%20Assad%20descended%20into%20civil%20war%2013%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Assad%2C%20who%20had%20crushed%20all%20forms%20of%20dissent%2C%20flew%20out%20of%20Damascus%20for%20an%20unknown%20destination%20earlier%20on%20Sunday%2C%20two%20senior%20army%20officers%20told%20Reuters%2C%20as%20rebels%20said%20they%20had%20entered%20the%20capital%20with%20no%20sign%20of%20army%20deployments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%2050%20years%20of%20oppression%20under%20Baath%20rule%2C%20and%2013%20years%20of%20crimes%20and%20tyranny%20and%20(forced)%20displacement...%20we%20announce%20today%20the%20end%20of%20this%20dark%20period%20and%20the%20start%20of%20a%20new%20era%20for%20Syria%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20rebel%20factions%20said%20on%20Telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Syrian%20army%20later%20said%20it%20was%20continuing%20operations%20against%20%26quot%3Bterrorist%20groups%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20key%20cities%20of%20Hama%20and%20Homs%20and%20in%20Deraa%20countryside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pace%20of%20events%20in%20Syria%20has%20stunned%20Arab%20capitals%20and%20raised%20fears%20of%20a%20new%20wave%20of%20regional%20instability.%C2%A0Clearly%2C%20the%20armed%20opposition%20forces%20took%20advantage%20of%20the%20change%20in%20the%20power%20balance%20caused%20by%20nearby%20wars--%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20in%20Lebanon%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael's%20war%20in%20Gaza%20and%20Lebanon%20has%20done%20significant%20damage%20to%20Mr%20Asaad's%20ally%20Iran's%20so-called%20axis%20of%20resistance%2C%20especially%20Hezbollah.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Russia%2C%20another%20stakeholder%20in%20Syria%2C%20is%20distracted%20by%20its%20fight%20in%20Ukraine%20making%20it%20harder%20to%20defend%20the%20Assad%20regime.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia's%20Stake%20In%20Syria%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lightning%20advance%20of%20rebels%20in%20Syria%20is%20threatening%20one%20of%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20proudest%20achievements%2C%20his%202015%20military%20intervention%20to%20save%20Bashar%20al-Assad's%20regime.%20The%20end%20of%20Mr%20Asaad's%20control%20in%20Syria%20risks%20not%20just%20Russia's%20prestige%2C%20but%20its%20coveted%20military%20foothold%20in%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%20region--%20the%20naval%20base%20of%20Tartus%20and%2C%20further%20north%2C%20the%20Hmeimim%20Air%20Base%2C%20both%20with%2049-year-leases%20received%20after%20Russia's%20regime-saving%20intervention%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2F12%2F06%2Frussia-syria-war-rebels-tartus-bases%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20using%20these%20bases%20to%20protect%20Mr%20Assad's%20fragile%20regime%2C%20Moscow%20has%20used%20them%20to%20challenge%20American%20supremacy%20by%20projecting%20its%20military%20power%20in%20the%20eastern%20Mediterranean%20and%20claiming%20the%20role%20of%20a%20world%20power%20with%20vital%20regional%20interests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20however%2C%20currently%20has%20its%20hands%20full%20with%20its%20war%20on%20Ukraine.%20As%20per%20an%20estimate%20by%20Britain's%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%2C%20November%20was%20the%20costliest%20month%20of%20the%20war%20so%20far%20for%20Moscow's%20forces%2C%20with%20an%20average%20of%20more%20than%201%2C500%20killed%20or%20wounded%20a%20day.%20Russia%20has%20been%20facing%20a%20Ukrainian%20incursion%20on%20its%20own%20soil%20since%20August%20that%20it%20is%20struggling%20to%20expel%2C%20now%20with%20the%20help%20of%20North%20Korean%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20amid%20the%20reports%20of%20the%20fall%20of%20Syria%2C%20Russia%20is%20at%20risk%20of%20losing%20control%20over%20the%20Hmeimim%20and%20Tartus%20bases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Could%20Fall%20Of%20Syria%20Impact%20Russia's%20War%20In%20Ukraine%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkyivindependent.com%2Ffall-of-aleppo-deals-blow-to-russias-middle-east-clout-may-indirectly-strengthen-ukraines-hand%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Kyiv%20Independent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Charles%20Lister%2C%20a%20Syria%20expert%20at%20the%20Middle%20East%20Institute%20said%20even%20during%20the%20war%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20Moscow%20never%20scaled%20its%20military%20presence%20back%20down.%20However%2C%20the%20quality%20of%20Russia's%20officer%20corps%20in%20Syria%20had%20declined.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20retains%20exactly%20the%20same%20troop%20levels.%20They've%20conducted%20the%20same%20number%20of%20air%20sorties%20over%20Syria%20with%20the%20same%20geographical%20breadth%20that%20they%20did%20prior%20to%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20speaking%20on%20the%20Lawfare%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20has%20changed%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20Russia%20can%20no%20longer%20count%20on%20the%20Wagner%20Group%2C%20which%20has%20played%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20safeguarding%20the%20Kremlin's%20interests%20in%20Syria%20in%20the%20past.%20Bogged%20down%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%20cannot%20send%20serious%20reinforcements%20to%20its%20military%20contingent%20in%20the%20Middle%20Eastern%20country%20either%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lowyinstitute.org%2Fthe-interpreter%2Frussia-loser-fall-syria-s-aleppo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Interpreter.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20its%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20has%20lost%20several%20allies%20from%20the%20Collective%20Security%20Treaty%20Organisation%20(CSTO).%20The%20end%20of%20Mr%20Asaad's%20regime%20could%20mean%20Russia%20loses%20Syria%20as%20well%2C%20forcing%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20eventually%20shut%20down%20its%20Khmeimim%20Air%20Base%20in%20the%20Latakia%20area%2C%20and%20the%20naval%20facility%20in%20Tartus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20two%20years%20of%20war%2C%20Moscow%20has%20redeployed%20weaponry%20from%20Syria%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20including%20Pantsir%20missile%20systems.%20Exposing%20its%20military%20and%20political%20weakness%20in%20Syria%20could%20undermine%20Russia's%20leverage%20in%20any%20potential%20negotiations%20surrounding%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fall%20of%20Aleppo%20has%20exposed%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20military%20overreach%20and%20has%20put%20its%20alliance%20with%20Iran%20under%20stress%20because%20of%20its%20competing%20military%20objectives%20in%20the%20country%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.euronews.com%2F2024%2F12%2F04%2Fsyria-how-the-conflict-could-impact-the-ukraine-crisis-and-migration%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEuro%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20thus%20keen%20on%20encouraging%20dialogue%20between%20Ankara%20and%20Damascus%20and%20has%20deployed%20diplomatic%20efforts%20to%20open%20trilateral%20negotiations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733645100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F61kuovo_syria-civil-war-afp_625x300_08_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-syrian-rebels-topple-assad-regime-how-it-may-impact-russia-ukrainewar-7199697%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20five%20decades%20of%20Baath%20rule%20in%20Syria%20ended%20on%20Sunday%20as%20Islamist-led%20rebels%20declared%20that%20they%20had%20taken%20Damascus%2C%20sending%20President%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20fleeing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-syrian-rebels-topple-assad-regime-how-it-may-impact-russia-ukrainewar-7199697%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Who's%20Who%20Of%20Al-Assads%3A%20Inside%20Syria's%20Most%20Powerful%20Family%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESyrian%20President%20Bashar%20Al-Assad%20has%20reportedly%20fled%20Damascus%2C%20signalling%20the%20end%20of%20his%20rule%20after%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20of%20brutal%20civil%20war.%20Rebel%20groups%2C%20including%20Hayat%20Tahrir%20al-Sham%2C%20have%20made%20significant%20advances%2C%20leaving%20the%20capital%20vulnerable%20and%20marking%20the%20collapse%20of%20Assad's%20once%20impenetrable%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20capital%2C%20now%20left%20vulnerable%2C%20stands%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20regime's%20sudden%20fall.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shifting%20power%20dynamics%20reflect%20the%20unravelling%20of%20a%20family%20dynasty%20that%20has%20defined%20Syria's%20fate%20for%20over%20half%20a%20century.%20Bashar%20Al-Assad%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Blast%20standing%26quot%3B.%20Often%20called%20%26quot%3Ba%20dictator%20without%20a%20dictator%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20power%20relied%20not%20just%20on%20his%20leadership%2C%20but%20on%20the%20unyielding%20support%20of%20his%20%26quot%3Binner%20circle%26quot%3B%2C%20his%20closest%20family%20members%20-%20his%20brother%20Maher%2C%20a%20fiery%20military%20commander%3B%20his%20sister%20Bushra%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Iron%20Lady%26quot%3B%3B%20and%20her%20husband%20Asef%20Shawkat%2C%20a%20calculating%20intelligence%20figure.%20But%20as%20Assad%20flees%2C%20their%20once-unified%20front%20begins%20to%20fracture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20key%20players%20within%20the%20regime's%20inner%20circle%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaher%20Al-Assad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFifty-six-year-old%20Maher%20al-Assad%2C%20Bashar's%20younger%20brother%2C%20commands%20Syria's%20Republican%20Guard%20and%20the%204th%20Armoured%20Division%2C%20making%20him%20a%20key%20figure%20in%20both%20Syria's%20military%20and%20its%20alliance%20with%20Iran.%20Known%20as%20the%20hardliner%20of%20the%20family%2C%20Maher%20is%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ruthless%20face%20of%20power%26quot%3B%20and%20oversees%20the%20Shabiha%20militia%2C%20which%20protects%20the%20Assad%20regime's%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanctioned%20by%20the%20EU%20in%202011%20for%20his%20role%20in%20violence%20against%20protesters%2C%20Maher's%20reputation%20for%20cruelty%20is%20reflected%20in%20protests%20that%20often%20target%20him%20directly.%20He%20has%20also%20been%20linked%20to%20the%201999%20shooting%20of%20his%20brother-in-law%2C%20Asef%20Shawkat%2C%20and%20named%20a%20suspect%20in%20the%202005%20assassination%20of%20Lebanese%20prime%20minister%20Rafik%20Hariri.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnisa%20Makhlouf%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnisa%20Makhlouf%2C%20widow%20of%20the%20late%20Syrian%20President%20Hafez%20al-Assad%20and%20mother%20of%20Bashar%2C%20may%20keep%20a%20low%20profile%2C%20but%20she%20holds%20the%20final%20say%20on%20all%20matters%20within%20the%20Assad%20family.%20%26quot%3BDecisions%20are%20made%20collectively%20in%20the%20family's%20inner%20circle%2C%20but%20Anisa%20has%20the%20last%20say%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wael%20al-Hafez%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Syrian%20opposition%20in%20exile%2C%20according%20to%20the%20feminist%20blog%20Les%20Martiennes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBushra%20Al-Assad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201960%2C%20Bushra%20Al-Assad%20is%20Bashar's%20only%20sister%20and%20a%20trained%20pharmacist.%20Like%20her%20brother%20Maher%2C%20she%20is%20known%20as%20a%20hawk%20within%20the%20regime%20and%20plays%20a%20significant%20role%20as%20Bashar's%20secretary.%20In%20the%20mid-1990s%2C%20she%20married%20Asef%20Shawkat.%20Bushra%20has%20also%20had%20a%20strained%20relationship%20with%20Bashar's%20wife%2C%20Asma.%20According%20to%20former%20Syrian%20diplomat%20Mohammed%20Daoud%2C%20Bushra%20long%20prevented%20Asma%20from%20assuming%20the%20title%20of%20Syria's%20%26quot%3BFirst%20Lady%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20title%20she%20preferred%20to%20keep%20with%20her%20mother%2C%20Anisa.%20She%20has%20business%20ties%20with%20Rami%20Makhlouf%2C%20Bashar's%20maternal%20cousin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERami%20Makhlouf%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERami%20Makhlouf%2C%20Bashar%20al-Assad's%20first%20cousin%2C%20controls%20about%2060%20per%20cent%20of%20Syria's%20business.%20Born%20in%201965%2C%20he's%20considered%20Syria's%20richest%20man%2C%20with%20interests%20in%20telecommunications%2C%20retail%2C%20energy%2C%20banking%2C%20and%20transportation.%20The%20US%20sanctioned%20him%20in%202008%20for%20abusing%20political%20influence%2C%20and%20the%20EU%20followed%20in%202011%2C%20accusing%20him%20of%20funding%20the%20crackdown%20on%20protesters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHated%20for%20corruption%2C%20Rami%20Makhlouf%20recently%20announced%20plans%20to%20donate%20part%20of%20his%20fortune%20to%20charity.%20His%20brother%2C%20Hafez%20Makhlouf%2C%20heads%20Syria's%20civilian%20intelligence%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsef%20Shawkat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeneral%20Asef%20Shawkat%2C%20an%20Alawite%20military%20officer%2C%20married%20Bashar%20al-Assad's%20sister%2C%20Bushra%2C%20in%201995.%20Initially%20rejected%20by%20the%20Assad%20family%2C%20he%20eventually%20gained%20their%20trust%20and%20built%20a%20close%20relationship%20with%20Bashar.%20Asef%20Shawkat%20quickly%20rose%20through%20the%20ranks%2C%20serving%20as%20Head%20of%20Military%20Intelligence%2C%20then%20Deputy%20Military%20Intelligence%20Chief%2C%20and%20later%20Chief%20of%20Military%20Intelligence%20until%202005.%20Despite%20facing%20international%20controversies%2C%20he%20was%20reassigned%20as%20Deputy%20Chief-of-Staff%20in%202008.%20He%2C%20along%20with%20Maher%20al-Assad%2C%20is%20linked%20to%20the%202005%20assassination%20of%20Lebanese%20Prime%20Minister%20Rafik%20Hariri.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsma%20Al-Assad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20London%20in%201975%20to%20a%20Syrian%20diplomat%20family%2C%20Asma%20Al-Assad%20married%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20in%20December%202000.%20The%20couple%20has%20three%20sons%3A%20Hafez%2C%20Zein%2C%20and%20Karim.%20Asma%20holds%20degrees%20in%20computer%20science%20and%20French%20literature%20from%20King's%20College%20London%20and%20worked%20in%20investment%20banking%20before%20marrying%20Bashar.%20She%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20shaping%20Bashar's%20image%20as%20a%20moderate%20reformer.%20In%202005%2C%20she%20launched%20an%20organisation%20to%20encourage%20Syrian%20youth%20to%20embrace%20%26quot%3Bactive%20citizenship.%26quot%3B%20Rumors%20suggest%20that%2C%20since%20the%20uprising%20began%2C%20Asma%20has%20exiled%20herself%20in%20London%20with%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733644200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F5dr2eku_assad-family-_625x300_08_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhos-who-of-the-al-assads-brother-maher-sister-bushra-her-husband-asef-shawkat-7199005%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Behind%20the%20smoke%20and%20chaos%20of%20Syria's%20ongoing%20turmoil%2C%20the%20Al-Assad%20family%20stands%20as%20the%20untouchable%20core%20--%20a%20dynasty%20that%20has%20moulded%20the%20country's%20fate%20for%20over%20half%20a%20century.%20At%20