ation%20enhances%20the%20wood%E2%80%99s%20resistance%20against%20fungal%20decay%2C%20a%20study%20found.%20When%20the%20environmental%20impacts%20of%20acetylated%20Scots%20pine%2C%20tropical%20hardwood%20(Azobe)%2C%20and%20non-renewable%20materials%20(steel%2C%20concrete)%20were%20compared%2C%20the%20results%20showed%20that%20acetylated%20wood%20has%20a%20considerably%20lower%20carbon%20footprint%20than%20steel%2C%20concrete%20and%20unsustainably%20sourced%20Azobe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArchitects%2C%20take%20notes%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Considering%20the%20material%20is%20wood%2C%20Vijay%20cautions%20that%20it%20should%20be%20sourced%20from%20sustainable%20forests.%20%E2%80%9CTrees%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F299507%2Feco-friendly-mud-red-stone-kerala-home-skylights-elliptical-windows-save-on-electric-bills%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enatural%20carbon%20sequesters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20when%20used%20in%20construction%2C%20wood%20can%20further%20lock%20in%20that%20sequestered%20carbon%20for%20decades.%20If%20sourced%20from%20fast-growing%20species%20like%20spruce%20or%20pine%2C%20and%20sustainable%2C%20replenishable%20forests%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20win-win.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Arunava%20Banerjee%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fijcsm.springeropen.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs40069-022-00569-x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUtilization%20of%20Solid%20Waste%20in%20the%20Production%20of%20Autoclaved%20Aerated%20Concrete%20and%20Their%20Effects%20on%20its%20Physio-mechanical%20and%20Microstructural%20Properties%3A%20Alternative%20Sources%2C%20Characterization%2C%20and%20Performance%20Insights%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20by%